TMS/DTS Sourcing Leader Job
02 May 2014 09:44 PM - UAE
Job Description: Job Number: 1947538Business: GE Oil & GasBusiness Segment: Oil & GasAbout Us: Posted Position Title: TMS/DTS Sourcing LeaderCareer Level: ExperiencedFunction: SourcingFunction Segment: SourcingLocation: United Arab EmiratesU.S. State, China or Canada Provinces: City: Abu DhabiPostal Code: Relocation Assistance: NoRole Summary/Purpose: The TMS/DTS Sourcing Leader demonstrates leadership in communicating business goals, programs, and processes for TMS/DTS business segments in MENAT. In this role you will use your experience or expertise to solve problems, develop and execute objectives for self and TMS/DTS sourcing team, and effect short-term and some long-term business goals.Essential Responsibilities: - Achieve lowest possible cost for material, balanced against optimum quality and schedule needs- Solicit and evaluate proposals employing appropriate negotiation, cost and price analysis techniques, using available expertise from supporting organizations; implement purchase contracts following applicable company and government regulations- Evaluate current and anticipated requirements, determine potential sources, obtain bids, and plan programs to meet business needs- Responsible for assigned geography to meet the requirements of the business- Perform continual market analysis and monitor supplier progress- Coordinate training of suppliers to accomplish business initiatives- Coordination procurement of assigned geography to meet the requirements of TMS/DTS business segments- Coordinate, help direct, as well as perform, all required functions from initiation of an intent to purchase through to satisfactory delivery of material or services- Assure that material/services will be delivered on schedule, at negotiated price and meet required quality standards- Initiate necessary action to assure best value is received, customer delivery requirements are met, and address any manufacturing problems at supplier's facility- Provide coordination and leadership in procurement activities for assigned geography, including development to Small Disadvantaged Business- Develop Talents through continuous coaching to assigned resources and ensuring agreed trainings for their professional growth- Support TMS/DTS Sourcing HQ and O&G Sourcing MENAT in rolling processes, tool, metric and reporting in order to improve Team efficiency and full alignment to HQ and O&G MENAT organizations.Qualifications/Requirements: "- Bachelors degree from an accredited university or college (or high school diploma/GED with at least 4 years of experience in a Sourcing environment)- At least 7 years of experience in a Sourcing position, including negotiation involvement"- Strong oral and written communication skills- Strong interpersonal and leadership skills- Proven analytical and problem solving skills, with sound judgment and a diplomatic attitude- Highly motivated team member / leader- Ability to make formal and appealing presentations "Additional Eligibility Qualifications: Desired Characteristics:
